The '''Acuario Nacional de Cuba''' (National Aquarium of Cuba) is an [[Public aquarium|aquarium]] in [[Havana]], [[Cuba]] established in 1960 to focus on "research and environmental education".<ref>Howard Norfolk, "A Visit to the National Aquarium of Cuba (Acuario Nacional de Cuba)". ''Aquarticles'', January 1994. Available {{cite web|url=http://www.aquarticles.com/articles/travel/Norfolk_CubaNatAqua.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-07-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100806171803/http://www.aquarticles.com/articles/travel/Norfolk_CubaNatAqua.html |archivedate=2010-08-06 |df= }}</ref> Displays include those of [[coral]] and other tropical species, as well as a [[dolphinarium]] and [[sea lion]] shows.
