{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} {{Infobox school | name = Gabriel Taapopi Senior Secondary School | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | motto = | established =1988 | opened = | type = Secondary school | district = [[Ongwediva]] | grades = 8–12 | superintendent = | principal = Eelu Sakaria | enrollment = 800+ | faculty = Commerce, Science, Natural science and Social Studies | campus_size = | colors = White, blue & black | location = [[Oshana Region]] | country = [[Namibia]] | coordinates = {{coord|17|46|2|S|15|45|38|E|type:edu_region:NA|display=inline,title}} | information = | website = | feeder_schools = }}
'''Gabriel Taapopi Senior Secondary School''', also known as '''GT''', is a governmental secondary school in [[Ongwediva]] in the [[Oshana Region]] of northern [[Namibia]]. The school opened its doors in 1988 and was officially inaugurated in 1989 by then [[SWAPO]] deputy education minister [[Buddy Wentworth]]. It is named after [[Gabriel Taapopi]]. Its principal is Eelu Sakaria.<ref>[http://www.schoolnet.na/projects/DVAC/Gabriel_Taapopi/index.html]</ref> The school is one of the top performing schools in the country.<ref>[http://sun.com.na/content/national-news/old-mutual-continues-award-namibia%E2%80%99s-best-schools Old Mutual continues to award Namibia’s best schools]. ''Namibian Sun'' (11 March 2013).</ref> It has around 800 learners and about 30 teachers. The school features a large computer laboratory, physical science and biology labs as well as sports grounds.
==Sports and entertainment== The school has incorporated a wide range of sport activities in it is curricula. It is successfully involved in national sports competitions of netball and soccer.<ref>[http://www.namibiansun.com/sports/ashipala-gabriel-taapopi-dominate-far-north-champs.57572 Ashipala, Gabriel Taapopi dominate Far North champs]. Namibian Sun (23 September 2013).</ref><ref>[http://www.inamibia.co.na/news/local/item/35843-oshana-s-a-team-allafrica-com.html ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140418220602/http://www.inamibia.co.na/news/local/item/35843-oshana-s-a-team-allafrica-com.html |date=18 April 2014 }}</ref> The school groomed good [[association football|football]] players, like Benson Shilongo, Esko Kavela, Benjamen Hauwanga and Johannes Iithete.
