{{BLP sources|date=May 2015}} {{Infobox person | name = Iren Dimitrova | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = 1950 | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|death date†|birth date†}} --> | death_place = | nationality = Bulgarian | other_names = | occupation = Pianist | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = }}
'''Iren Dimitrova''' ([[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]]: Ирен Димитрова) (born 1950) is a [[Bulgaria]]n piano player and tutor of piano accompaniment and chamber music.
==Life== Dimitrova studied at the [[National Academy of Music (Bulgaria)|National Music Academy]] of [[Bulgaria]] in the piano class of prof. P. [[:bg:Панка Пелишек|Pelishek]], after which she specialised in chamber music and piano accompaniment at the Russian Academy of Music [[Gnessin State Musical College|Gnesin]], Moscow where she received her PhD. She enjoyed a long performance and teaching career, and taught chamber music and piano accompaniment in the National Art School of Varna,<ref>http://varnasummerfest.org/participants_bg_2.php?page=news_show_search&newsID=337&nsID=12</ref> piano at the [[Varna Free University]] "Chernorizets Hrabar", at the [[Shumen University|University of Shumen]] "Constantine of Preslav" and the Higher Institute of Music of Sfax. Dimitrova is one of the first pedagogues in Bulgaria who dedicated their life to the piano accompaniment and chamber music teaching and her activity greatly contributed to the development of these disciplines in the country. In 2011 she was honoured with the Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref>http://www.ubmd.org/static_info.php?id=18</ref>
