The '''École nationale des sciences appliquées de Tanger'''(ENSAT) located in [[Tangier]] the capital of the northern region of [[Morocco]], is a Moroccan engineering school created through a partnership between the University Abdelmalek Essaâdi and [[Institut National des Sciences Appliquées de Lyon|INSA de Lyon]]. 

It is a public establishment,training state engineers with general specializations in : telecommunication systems & networks, Computer Engineering, Electronic Systems Engineering and Control, and Industrial Engineering & logistics. It is known to be the first of the [[Écoles nationales des sciences appliquées|ENSA]]s

